[Student "S"]
{SOUTH's 2\C bid is Stayman, asking for a 4-card Major.

NORTH's 2\D bid denies four cards in either Major.

SOUTH knows there is no 8-card Major fit. He also knows the partnership has at least 26 points 
so he bids 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:QT.KQ93.A52.AT86 A63.A72.JT96.QJ3 KJ8754.86.KQ3.72 92.JT54.874.K954"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1NT pass 2H pass 2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "2c7eaaa8410fbe6e0413a3374bb9c37bffdaa1e168b5b1fb1e8b885962102b2b"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST, with 11 points and six \Ss, knows immediately that the final contract will be 4\S 
since the partners must have at least eight \Ss and at least 26 points.

She concludes that it might be better for EAST to be the Declarer so she bids 2\H 
as a Jacoby Transfer. When EAST makes the required 2\S bid she just bids 4\S which 
closes the auction with EAST as Declarer.}

